The Eastern Cape Department of Transport has cautioned motorists to be extra vigilant on the province’s roads due to the inclement weather. This as the South African Weather Services issued a warning that the province will experience bad weather over the next few days.  SA Weather | Saturday 09 April 2022   Provincial Transport Spokesperson, Unathi Binqose says traffic officers are on the ground monitoring the situation. “We’d like to issue a warning to road users in the Eastern Cape and motorist in particular to be extra cautious on the roads as conditions are wet and slippery rainy conditions engulfed our province in some parts of the province which makes visibility poor .We have seen accidents happening, thankfully none have been serious or have been deadly at this stage and we would like to keep it that way. We are issuing a warning to road users in particular to play their part and our road users will do the same,” says Binqose. Earlier ,the South African Weather Service issued a warning for freezing temperatures and heavy rains in parts of the Eastern Cape especially along the coast over the weekend. The rains may result in flooding in some low lying areas. Ayabonga Tshungwana from the South African weather services says this is due to a cut off low that is sitting over the interior of the country. Eastern Cape Tomorrow ‘s Weather overview: 10.4.2022 pic.twitter.com/2UZYfMKL1o — SA Weather Service (@SAWeatherServic) April 9, 2022 